Name: ATK LQ9-LB-1 Chevy LQ9 365CI/6.0L Base Engine 550HP
Description:
This is an LQ9 based engine with LS3 Aluminum heads making a very streetable 550HP+. Expect big mid to upper end power, will have a noticeable idle. For optimal Performance you will need headers, chassis dyno tune and 36lb injectors. Your engine may not necessarily come with all components listed, but they are listed as our recommendations of parts to run for optimal performance.

Engine Specifications:

  • HP: 550
  • TQ: 490
  • Block: New GM 6.0L Iron Gen IV
  • Bore/Stroke: 4.000” x 3.622”
  • Displacement (cu.in): 364
  • Crankshaft: OE reground 3.622” internally balanced 24 tooth
  • Rods: Scat 4340 forged I beam 6.125” with ARP 8740 bolts
  • Pistons: Manley forged 10.3:1 compression
  • Rings: Moly
  • Camshaft: Hyd. Roller
  • Cam Specs: Custom performance grind
  • Lifters: GM LS7
  • Timing Chain: Billet HD .250” roller
  • Cylinder Heads: GM LS3 aluminum 68.4cc/260cc 2.165”/1.590” valves
  • Rocker Arms: OE 1.7 ratio
  • Oil Pump: Melling

    Recommended Components:

  • Flexplate/Flywheel: Stock internally balanced
  • Balancer: Stock internally balanced/per application
  • Intake Manifold: Stock/Aftermarket EFI intake or Carbureted setup
  • Water Pump: Per application
  • Fuel Pump: Electric per application
  • Fuel Injectors: 36lb injectors
  • Spark Plugs: NGK #3186
  • Spark Plug Wires: Factory

    Engine Info:

  • Oil: Conventional / Non Synthetic 10W30
  • Oil Filter: Wix or K and N
  • Timing: Set to factory specifications via PCM module (ECM TUNING REQUIRED).
  • Spark Plug Gap: .040”
  • Firing Order: 18726543
  • Octane: 91+
  • Stall Converter: 2500+
  • Exhaust: 1 5/8 + Headers

    Notes: This engine can be swapped into a 2001-2007 6.0L application with a Gen III to Gen IV conversion kit or any other factory LS equipped vehicle. It can also be retrofitted for aftermarket EFI/Carb setups. ECM MUST BE TUNED, not doing so can damage the engine. A PCV valve must be ran; please follow the valve cover instructions provided. You must also run an Air-Oil separator system such as the Moroso #85487 to capture the excess crankcase vapors LS engines are known for. If you are not running a MAP Sensor, the MAP timing option in the timing control box must be zeroed out all the way across. Failure to do so will allow the controller to add timing which can lead to detonation. You must also run some sort of a steam line kit that dumps to your water pump, radiator or radiator hose; we recommend a 4 corner setup like the Trick Flow #TFS-306SB601. This allows air pockets/hot spots to escape the heads and can also be used to purge out trapped air when filling the radiator for the first time.

    Disclaimer: The parts listed are ATK’s recommendations of parts to be used to obtain our power figures listed. Power figures can vary based on parts used by the end user. It is the customer’s responsibility to verify components will work in their application. Some modifications to the vehicle may be required using these and or other aftermarket parts. . ATK reserves the right to substitute parts used in engines if necessary.

Name: ATK SPE4271500 Dart LS Next 427CI 1500HP Rated Short Block
Description:
ATK's new Elite Series LS Short Blocks are a step of above the rest. Every engine is a well thought out parts combination that is purpose built for each application.

Engine Specifications:

  • Block: Dart SHP LS Next Cast Iron
  • Bore/Stroke: 4.125" x 4.000"
  • Displacement (cu.in): 427 CID
  • Crankshaft: Dart Billet 58 tooth reluctor wheel
  • Rods: Manley H Tuff H Beam 6.125" ARP 2000 bolts
  • Pistons: JE Ultra 17.4cc Dish 2618 Forged with Thermal Coating, Lateral Gas Ports, .200″ Pin
  • Rings: JE Pro Seal with Carbon Steel Top Ring
  • Compression Ratios: 66cc= 10.4:1 / 68cc= 10.2:1 / 70cc= 10.0:1 (with .044″ gasket)
  • Camshaft Bearings: Installed and Clocked to OEM Position
  • Freeze Plugs: Installed and Sealed
  • Oil Galley Plugs: Installed and Sealed

Recommended Components:

  • Balancer- Internal balance
  • Flex plate/ Flywheel- Internal balance
  • Head Gasket: .051" or per application
  • Oil Pump: Melling #10296 with high pressure spring

Engine Info:

  • Oil: 20W50 Non synthetic for first 3000 miles
  • Oil Filter: Wix or K and N per application
  • Oil Pump: Melling 10296 with red spring

Feature and Benefits

  • Dart LS Next SHP Skirted Block – The Dart block features a full skirt design with a priority main oiling system, steel four bolt main caps and is setup to run a 4 or 6 bolt cylinder head.
  • Dart BILLET Crankshaft – The Dart Billet crankshafts are proven to handle over 2000HP and outfitted with Center Counter Weights. The CCW not only add material and strength to the center of the crank, but they also add balance and stability that counters the jump rope effect under high RPM and increased power.
  • Manley H Tuff H Beam Connecting Rods – Manley's H Tuff Rods have become the benchmark for fully machined high end connecting rods in the performance industry. These Rods include double-ribbed pin surround and increased cross sectional thickness in critical areas; for a connecting rod that will handle higher boost and horsepower levels than a standard H Beam Rod.
  • JE Ultra Series Pistons – The Ultra line combines all the best, most desirable piston features, such as thermal barrier crown coating, lateral gas ports, thick – wall wrist pins and a new forging technology for the ultimate strength. They are specifically designed for Massive Power and Boost right out of the box.
  • JE Pro Steel Rings – The JE Pro Steel Rings are designed to maximize horsepower through precision sealing of combustion pressure. This ring pack will have a carbon steel top ring for high boost applications.
  • Clevite H Bearings – These bearings were primarily developed for Nascar racing, but are well suited for High Performance applications as well. They're especially good for high revving engines and getting the exact clearances needed with consistency.
  • Suitable for a Single or Twin Turbo application!
  • Custom builds available!

    Notes: This engine can be used as an upgrade for the 2001-2007 Chevy trucks with the LQ4 6.0L or swapped into many other applications. ECM MUST BE TUNED, not doing so can damage the engine. : A PCV valve must be ran; please follow the valve cover instructions provided. You must also run an Air-Oil separator system such as the Moroso #85487 to capture the excess crankcase vapors LS engines are known for. If you are not running a MAP Sensor, the MAP timing option in the timing control box must be zeroed out all the way across. Failure to do so will allow the controller to add timing which can lead to detonation. You must also run some sort of a steam line kit that dumps to your water pump, radiator or radiator hose; we recommend a 4 corner setup like the Trick Flow #TFS-306SB601. This allows air pockets/hot spots to escape the heads and can also be used to purge out trapped air when filling the radiator for the first time.

    Notes: This engine can replace the 1999-2007 Chevy 5.3L LM7 engine with supporting modifications or any other factory LS equipped vehicle. It can also be retrofitted for aftermarket EFI/Carb setups. ECM MUST BE TUNED, not doing so can damage the engine. : A PCV valve must be ran; please follow the valve cover instructions provided. You must also run an Air-Oil separator system such as the Moroso #85487 to capture the excess crankcase vapors LS engines are known for. If you are not running a MAP Sensor, the MAP timing option in the timing control box must be zeroed out all the way across. Failure to do so will allow the controller to add timing which can lead to detonation. You must also run some sort of a steam line kit that dumps to your water pump, radiator or radiator hose; we recommend a 4 corner setup like the Trick Flow #TFS-306SB601. This allows air pockets/hot spots to escape the heads and can also be used to purge out trapped air when filling the radiator for the first time.
